description: Product Description SPLIT DEER ANTLER CHEWS ARE SAFE. OUR ANTLER CHEWS ARE SAFE. Primary Pets do NOT use any Chemicals When Cleaning Antlers. They are Pressure Washed with Clean Water Then Cut to Size and Hand Sanded to Eliminate any Splinters. ANTLER CHEWS. NATURAL AND SUSTAINABLE. ANTLER CHEWS. NATURAL AND SUSTAINABLE. All Dogs Have a Natural Need to Chew and Our Antler Chews Keep Your Dog Happy, Healthy and Entertained. Red Deer Antlers are One of the Most Natural and Environmentally Sustainable Products Available Anywhere. Primary Pets Antler Chews are Naturally Shed, Responsibly Sourced and Collected from Forests. ANTLER CHEWS ARE HEALTHY. ANTLER CHEWS ARE HEALTHY. Antler Chews are a Great Way to Keep Your Dog’s Teeth Strong and Clean – The Act of Chewing Helps to Reduce Tartar and Plaque. Antlers Contain Calcium, Chondroitin (Found in All Good Joint Care Supplements), Phosphorous, Manganese and Zinc so They’re perfect for Helping Develop Bone and Keep Teeth Strong. LOTS OF CHOICE. LOTS OF CHOICE. Our Antler Chews come in Various Shapes and Sizes to Suit any Dog. Please Remember that Every Antler is Different so May Not look Like the Examples in The Images. Please Note, Antlers are Purchased by Weight Rather Than Length or Thickness. Preparation -To prepare antlers into chews we take important stages to ensure highest quality & nutritious treats. CLEANING All antlers are ONLY pressure washed with water (no chemicals are used) to remove any residue of dirt or discoloration from leafs/moss. CUTTING This stage is only done by professional trained staff to ensure quality & equal sizes of chews. All unwanted 'spiky' antlers tips are removed for dog's safety while chewing . SANDING The first thing when we thought about making antler dog chews was how to make it SAFE. Safety is our biggest value. By sanding sharp edges & uneven surface we will ensure there is no danger or discomfort for the dog while chewing. Dog Chew Antlers are safe chews for dog to enjoy and keep a good dental health. Sustainably Sourced They are cruelty -free and sustainable chews collected from forests. Made in the UK We use 100% naturally shedded British antlers , collected in the highlands of Scotland. Rich in Nutrients Marrow in antlers is rich in calcium and protein, making it a healthy dog treat
